comments[13]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-04T05:40:59.863Z",codex-sdk-surface,"Sidecar SDK surface evidence: added activateExtensionForTest to @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk/testing and the SDK barrel, documented the package-author pattern in docs/SDK.md and docs/EXTENSIONS.md, and covered command/hook activation plus missing-capability failure in tests/unit/sdk-index.spec.ts. Verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/sdk-index.spec.ts (23 tests), pnpm build, and manual temp npm consumer installing <repo-root> then importing @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk/testing returned {ok:true,command:'consumer hello',failed:0,warnings:0}. Note: unrelated concurrent worktree changes exist for pm-vnjh/docs/TESTING.md/package.json/scripts/smoke-external-packages.mjs and were not modified by this sidecar."
  "2026-06-04T07:11:34.479Z",sdk-docs-subagent,"Subagent findings for GitHub #107 afterCommand before/after item state (read-only; no source edits):\n\nScope/lineage:\n- GitHub issue #107 is open and belongs under existing SDK/package platform epic pm-ugqx; do not create a duplicate pm item unless implementation needs a child task at claim time.\n- This is distinct from closed pm-e9ut/#104: onWrite now has item-aware before/after snapshots, but afterCommand remains command-level only.\n\nCurrent surfaces:\n- src/core/extensions/extension-types.ts defines BeforeCommandHookContext and AfterCommandHookContext. AfterCommandHookContext currently has ok/error/result only; result is unknown and has no typed affected item state.\n- src/sdk/index.ts re-exports AfterCommandHookContext, ItemDocument, ItemFrontMatter, and ItemStatus, so additive type changes there flow to package authors automatically.\n- src/core/extensions/extension-hook-runtime.ts clones hook contexts before dispatch; any new payload must stay plain structured data.\n- src/cli/main.ts runAndClearAfterCommandHooks constructs the afterCommand event from active command metadata plus getActiveCommandResult(); this is the single command-wrapper insertion point.\n- src/core/extensions/index.ts only stores activeCommandResult today. It has no mutation-state accumulator.\n- src/cli/register-mutation.ts and src/cli/register-operations.ts call mutate commands then invalidate search and print results. Existing result shapes expose item/changed_fields/ids, but not previous item snapshots.\n- src/core/store/item-store.ts mutateItem/deleteItem already has beforeDocument/afterDocument and dispatches them to onWrite for update/delete/history writes.\n- src/cli/commands/create.ts has beforeDocument/afterDocument and changedFields for create onWrite events.\n- src/cli/commands/restore.ts and src/sdk/package-import-adapters.ts were recently enriched for onWrite and should be mirrored if afterCommand should cover restore/import.\n- src/cli/commands/update.ts has local previousStatus for status-specific logic, but the durable source of truth is mutateItem before/after snapshots.\n\nMinimal implementation shape:\n- Add optional typed field to AfterCommandHookContext, preferably affected_items?: Array<{ id: string; type?: string; previous_status?: ItemStatus; status?: ItemStatus; before?: ItemDocument; after?: ItemDocument; changed_fields?: string[]; op?: string; path?: string }>.\n- Keep result unchanged for compatibility; do not ask package authors to parse unknown result for transition detection.\n- Reuse the same item mutation snapshots already produced for onWrite. Best small architecture: add an active per-command mutation accumulator in src/core/extensions/index.ts (for example recordActiveCommandItemMutation/consumeActiveCommandItemMutations) and call it from the same item-write sites that invoke runActiveOnWriteHooks. Then src/cli/main.ts adds affected_items to the afterCommand context.\n- Dedupe history/item write pairs so package authors see one logical mutation per item/op, not both update and update:history. Use op without :history as the canonical event and include path if useful.\n- For update-many, afterCommand should naturally include all updated items because each runUpdate call records into the active command accumulator. For dry-run/rollback, decide explicitly: dry-run should probably omit affected_items; rollback should include restored before/after where available.\n- For close via update auto-route, affected_items should show the final close transition, and if pre-update fields ran first it may either include two entries for the same id or a merged entry. Package-author ergonomics favors merging by id with before from first mutation, after from last mutation, changed_fields union, op such as update+close or close.\n\nDocs to update:\n- docs/SDK.md near the hook registration section should document afterCommand affected_items, transition examples, optionality, and the difference from onWrite. Guidance: use afterCommand for command-level notifications and onWrite for low-level file sync.\n- docs/EXTENSIONS.md Runtime APIs should mention afterCommand affected_items alongside onWrite fields.\n- packages/pm-lifecycle-hooks/README.md and extensions/lifecycle-hooks/index.ts can stay default-inert, or optionally show a commented/README example that checks event.affected_items?.some(item => item.previous_status !== item.status). Keep the package behavior inert.\n\nTests to add/update:\n- tests/unit/extensions-runtime.spec.ts: verify afterCommand enriched context is cloned/isolated and minimal contexts without affected_items still work.\n- tests/unit/sdk-index.spec.ts: compile/import the new AfterCommandHookContext shape from @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk with ItemDocument/ItemStatus fields.\n- tests/unit/item-store.spec.ts or a new focused unit test: if adding an accumulator, assert mutateItem/deleteItem records logical mutation snapshots without exposing history duplicates.\n- tests/integration/cli.integration.spec.ts near existing afterCommand hook tests: install a temp extension that logs event.affected_items for create, update --status, close, delete, and failed get. Assert success commands include before/status/after/status and failed commands omit affected_items while still running with ok=false.\n- Add focused coverage for update-many applying status changes to multiple items if accumulator design is used.\n\nCompatibility and UX risks:\n- Additive optional field is safe for existing hooks; do not make affected_items required.\n- Payload size can grow for large bodies or bulk update-many. Consider including full before/after ItemDocument only for affected_items and documenting that heavy consumers should filter by changed_fields/status. If this becomes too expensive, a lean alternative is previous/current metadata snapshots plus body omitted by default, but issue #107 asks for front-matter snapshot so metadata-only may be enough.\n- Naming should be stable and agent-friendly. Prefer snake_case to match pm output fields: affected_items, previous_status, changed_fields.\n- Avoid deriving previous_status from command options; command options cannot distinguish reopen/open/unblock correctly. Derive from before.metadata.status and after.metadata.status.\n- Failed commands should still run afterCommand with ok=false, but should not contain stale accumulator state; clear/consume state in postAction/finally.\n- Extension hooks are cloned via cloneContextSnapshot, so keep documents JSON-serializable and avoid class instances, Dates, Errors, Maps, or functions.\n\nRecommended first implementation slice:\n1. Add AfterCommandAffectedItem type and affected_items? to extension-types.ts, exported through SDK barrel automatically.\n2. Add active command mutation accumulator helpers in src/core/extensions/index.ts.\n3. Record logical item mutations from create, mutateItem, deleteItem, restore, and package import alongside existing onWrite dispatch.\n4. Include consumed affected_items in src/cli/main.ts afterCommand context and clear it on no-runtime/failure paths.\n5. Document SDK/extension guidance and add the tests above."
  "2026-06-06T18:31:36.140Z",sdk-ergonomics-subagent,"SDK ergonomics subagent evidence: recommended and applied small package-author slice in packages/pm-lifecycle-hooks/README.md. Added copyable afterCommand event.affected transition filtering pattern so notification/cache packages can use command-level mutation context without parsing result payloads or reading item files. Linked doc path and verification. Verification passed: pnpm build. Note: observed separate in-progress child pm-01bm claimed by codex-sdk-continuation; left untouched."
  "2026-06-06T18:31:39.078Z",coverage-subagent,"Coverage subagent read-only findings (2026-06-06): duplicate check reused existing SDK/package platform epic pm-ugqx; no new pm item created. Current afterCommand affected item context has integration coverage in tests/integration/extension-hooks.integration.spec.ts for create/update/restore/delete and focused smoke coverage passes. Smallest uncovered/fragile patch target is tests/unit/extensions-runtime.spec.ts: add direct unit coverage for recordAfterCommandAffectedItem(), consumeAfterCommandAffectedItems(), and projectAfterCommandItemSnapshot() in src/core/extensions/index.ts. Rationale: src/core/extensions/index.ts is explicitly excluded from coverage thresholds in vitest.config.ts, and existing integration coverage only exercises the accumulator/projector indirectly through CLI commands; branch cases remain fragile: no registered afterCommand hooks should skip recording, consume should clear the accumulator, unset:* changed fields should project the canonical field, omitted heavy fields like body/comments/tests should stay out of afterCommand snapshots, and non-string changed_fields entries should be ignored. Existing checks run by subagent: PM_AUTHOR=coverage-subagent pm context --limit 10; pm search \"SDK CLI context management coverage fragile\" --limit 10; pm list-open --limit 20; pm list-in-progress --limit 20; pm get pm-ugqx --full; pm get pm-mpbb --full; rg inspections for afterCommand/affected coverage; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/extension-hooks.integration.spec.ts (1 passed); node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/extensions-runtime.spec.ts tests/unit/sdk-index.spec.ts (38 passed); npm install -g .; pm --version => 2026.6.6; node -v => v25.9.0; pnpm -v => 10.33.4; pnpm build passed. Recommended focused verification after patch: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/extensions-runtime.spec.ts tests/integration/extension-hooks.integration.spec.ts tests/unit/sdk-index.spec.ts; optional full gate: node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage."
  "2026-06-06T18:32:16.426Z",github-triage-subagent,"Dependency/security triage 2026-06-06: gh Dependabot open alerts returned empty; vulnerability alerts endpoint returned 204 enabled; latest fixed Dependabot alerts are brace-expansion/vite only. pnpm audit --audit-level moderate reported no known vulnerabilities. pnpm security:scan reported no credential-like secrets in tracked files. pnpm outdated --format json reports only commander current 14.0.3 latest 15.0.0 wanted 14.0.3; npm view commander@15.0.0 engines shows node >=22.12.0 while package.json declares node >=20, so do not bump commander unless the package support floor moves past Node 20 or a compatible commander release appears."
  "2026-06-08T13:20:25.849Z",maintainer-agent,"Starting bundled PR 'Extension SDK platform maturity' (branch feat/extension-sdk-maturity-flags-identity-lifecycle). In-scope items: pm-ltbr (FlagDefinition list/default typed + accumulation parity), pm-oll8 (field-type did-you-mean validation), pm-qo36 (api.extension self-identity), pm-k1e4 (deactivate lifecycle hook + MCP teardown), pm-aw7d (testing override/parser/preflight/renderer assertion helpers), pm-z9ho (manifest resource kinds assets/prompts). pm-l0jd value_type/type unification folded into pm-ltbr; manifest JSON Schema + getWorkspaceContracts memoization remain open under pm-l0jd. Core API work driven directly; pm-aw7d and pm-z9ho delegated to isolated sub-agents."
  "2026-06-28T04:39:30.513Z",codex-cli-agent,"Implementation start: duplicate-safe orientation checked active in-progress/open items, GitHub PR/issues/security surfaces, and all-status SDK/package search. Reusing canonical package platform epic pm-ugqx for a package-author scaffold validation improvement; no duplicate item created."
  "2026-06-28T04:41:53.439Z",codex-cli-agent,"Tracker hygiene: replaced stale linked test path tests/unit/sdk-index.spec.ts with relocated tests/unit/sdk/sdk-index.spec.ts after pm test surfaced a false missing-file failure."
  "2026-06-28T04:56:39.495Z",codex-cli-agent,"Implementation evidence: package scaffolds now generate npm scripts with typecheck, test:runtime, and a self-validating npm test that runs typecheck before node:test. README guidance for declarative and imperative package scaffolds now makes npm test the default package-author validation gate and documents test:runtime for tight loops."
  "2026-06-28T04:56:39.883Z",codex-cli-agent,"Verification evidence: pnpm build passed; focused scaffold tests passed; pm test pm-ugqx --run --progress passed 4/4 after stale relocated SDK test links were corrected; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed 256 files, 5138 tests, coverage 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-06-28T04:56:40.319Z",codex-cli-agent,"Manual temp smoke: in /tmp/pm-scaffold-smoke.ceJQsN with sandboxed PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH, ran pm init . --force --defaults, pm package init context-kit --project --declarative, npm install, npm test, npm run test:runtime, pm package install, pm package doctor --project --detail deep --json, and pm context kit ping. Result: npm test ran typecheck plus runtime tests, package doctor status ok with zero warnings, generated command executed."
  "2026-06-28T04:56:40.770Z",codex-cli-agent,"GitHub/release evidence: no open PRs; open issue #374 remains the known external RELEASE_PAT scheduled-release blocker; open Dependabot alerts []; secret-scanning alerts []; pnpm audit reports no known vulnerabilities; pm-changelog 2026.6.27 generated CHANGELOG.md unchanged; pm health summary ok with zero warnings; validate history drift ok with existing closed-item resolution metadata warnings; Sentry gate zero critical/high and telemetry best-effort ok with 0.76% finish error rate."
  "2026-06-28T05:04:37.981Z",codex-cli-agent,"Review response: cubic identified that the shared canonical package-platform epic should not remain claimed/in_progress after this PR. Returning pm-ugqx to open and releasing the claim so future package-platform work can reuse the lineage without ownership friction."
